      "faqs": [
        {
          "question": "When is an Ultrasound advisable to be done? ",
          "answer": "If there is a requirement for an abdominal ultrasound, fasting must be done in order to create clean images where only the internal organs are captured. Rest instructions and procedures can be sought from a physician."
        },
        {
          "question": "Can we find any ultrasound-related services in Bangalore? ",
          "answer": "We are proud to inform the readers now that Cadabam’s Diagnostics in Bangalore provides ultrasound services to facilitate identifying and monitoring medical conditions."
        },
        {
          "question": "What Is a Normal Ultrasound Result? ",
          "answer": "A normal ultrasound result states that the internal organs and soft tissues reasonably work there is no presence of any abnormalities such as masses, fluid accumulation, or structural changes among other factors. However, it is worth remembering that “normal” does differ slightly from one person to another due to their age, gender or even health. This doesn't mean however that someone should cease to consult their healthcare official."
        },
        {
          "question": "Who Performs an Ultrasound Scan? ",
          "answer": "Sonographers are trained professionals who operate ultrasound machines and target specific areas of the body with the equipment in order to create usable photographs of the location for diagnosis."
        },
        {
          "question": "How Safe Is an Ultrasound Scan? ",
          "answer": "Ultrasound scans are safe since they use sound waves instead of radiation. They do not breach the skin in any way or form. There also are no potential dangers that are known in existence. This makes ultrasounds guess-free scans for pregnant women and for other clinics."
        }
