    "markdown": "a non-invasive imaging technique that uses high-frequency sound waves to create pictures of the inside of the body\n\n## Ultrasound Overview\n\n![Ultrasound Overview](https://cadabams-diagnostics-assets.s3.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com/cadabam_assets/image-1731735946889-414492423.jpg)\n\nUltrasound, sonography or ultrasonography as it is also called, is a painless diagnostic imaging technique that uses ultrasound waves to create moving images of the internal organs including soft parts of the body. It can be used for a wide range of scanning ranging from monitoring pregnancies to diagnosing diseases.\n\nIts imaging capabilities allow doctors to see through your body without making the cut and it does not employ radiation as X-ray machines do.\n\n### What is An Ultrasound Scan?\n\nUltrasound essentially involves the use of sound waves with a frequency higher than 20kHz to analyze or get images of internal organs of a human body. It is a powerful tool which helps doctors detect abnormalities in tissues and organs. The ultrasound is made up of a device known as a transducer which produces and receives sound waves and indirectly forms images.\n\n## Types of Ultrasounds\n\nThere are different types of ultrasound scans that are used for various conditions and parts of the body. Among these, some of the most common types of ultrasounds are: -\n\n**Abdominal Ultrasound:** This is an ultrasound done to look for blood vessels and organs in your lower abdominal region and to check for conditions like gallbladder stones, kidney stones, and liver problems.\n\n**Pelvic Ultrasound:** Pelvic Ultrasound is probably the most popular type of ultrasound, as every woman have had this type of ultrasound at least once in their life. This is most used to diagnose pregnancy, to assess if a fetus is developing properly, to look for the presence of abdominal organs in females like the uterus and ovaries and in males the bladder and many more.\n\n**Musculoskeletal Ultrasound:** Musculoskeletal Ultrasound is very helpful in detecting troubles with tendons, ligaments or muscles.\n\n**Doppler Ultrasound:** It is a special type of ultrasound scan in which the blood flow through arteries and veins is used to be tested for the presence of vascular disorders such as blood clots.\n\n**Fetal Ultrasound:** Fetal Ultrasound is used in pregnancy to keep track of baby development and baby’s health. It helps in tracking the growth of the fetus, checking if there are any abnormalities, and measuring the amount of amniotic fluid.\n\n## Risks & Limitations of the Ultrasound Test\n\n![Risks & Limitations of the Ultrasound Test](https://cadabams-diagnostics-assets.s3.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com/cadabam_assets/image-1731735954619-142663100.png)\n\nIn terms of the dangers involved with getting an ultrasound test, these are largely negligible as it employs no radiation whilst producing images, thus, it is regarded as one of the best and least hazardous diagnostic procedures.\n\nOne of the important issues regarding the applicability of ultrasound scanning is that, it may not be suitable for those regions of the body that lie within gas cavities e.g. the intestines, or the bones cover them up. Also, other factors such as obesity may affect the ultrasound’s accuracy.\n\n## List of Parameters Considered During the Scan\n\n![List of Parameters Considered During the Scan](https://cadabams-diagnostics-assets.s3.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com/cadabam_assets/image-1731735965281-669880283.png)\n\nIt is important to understand that the parameters may vary depending on the type of ultrasound and the purpose of the scan. However, here are a few common parameters that are measured during an ultrasound scan:\n\n- Any change regarding the size, form or dilatation of organs or tissues\n- When Doppler ultrasound is performed, evaluation of blood circulation and the states of vascular system\n- Obstruction of organs which might include cysts or tumours or any other formations\n- For prenatal scanning – amniotic fluid level measurement and checking growth parameters of the fetus (for example: biparietal diameter)\n\n## Reasons for Taking the Ultrasound\n\n![Reasons for Taking the Ultrasound](https://cadabams-diagnostics-assets.s3.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com/cadabam_assets/image-1731735971667-920239951.png)\n\nThere are multiple reasons that your doctor may suggest you take an ultrasound scan, some of them include: -\n\n**Diagnosing Abnormalities**: In a variety of instances, an ultrasound is used to help diagnose the cyst, tumor or even other surrounding organs’ abnormalities.\n\n**Pregnancy Care:** The ultrasound allows doctors to examine the fetus, while also gauging its state of health.\n\n**Investigating Pain or Swelling**: When there is swelling, pain or other symptoms that are hard to explain, this is where the ultrasound scanning technique comes in.\n\n**Evaluating Organ Function:** Conditions that involve gall bladder disease, kidney stones or cirrhosis of the liver can be evaluated through ultrasound imaging.\n\n### When and Who Needs to Take an Ultrasound Scan?\n\nUltrasounds are recommended to patients for a variety of reasons, some of them include: -\n\n- If your doctor suspects issues with your internal organs such as the liver, kidney, or heart.\n- Pregnant women for evaluating the conditions of the fetuses.\n- Athletes identify musculoskeletal injuries like tendon ruptures or sprains.\n- Patients with no result of visceral massage and other techniques with swelling, pain, or complications of the visceral organs.\n- People with heart disease.\n- Patients with gallstones suspect suffering from kidney stones or some other organ related disorders.\n\n## Benefits of Taking the Ultrasound\n\n![Benefits of Taking the Ultrasound](https://cadabams-diagnostics-assets.s3.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com/cadabam_assets/image-1731735980742-820179332.png)\n\nUltrasound scan offers a range of benefits and due to this, it is widely used to assess the variety of diseases and monitor a fetus. Some of the benefits include: -\n\n**Non-Invasive:** There is no requirement of any needles or incisions to perform an ultrasound. Such procedures are needed for biopsies and surgeries.\n\n**No Radiation:** This is a feature that helps to protect pregnant mothers and others who must undergo so many scans.\n\n**Real-Time Imaging**: The real time imaging of an ultrasound scan enables medical professionals to fully fathom the insides of a person’s organs and be able to diagnose any abnormalities instantly.\n\n## Illnesses Diagnosed with Ultrasound\n\n![Illnesses Diagnosed with Ultrasound](https://cadabams-diagnostics-assets.s3.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com/cadabam_assets/image-1731735986278-403634312.png)\n\nUltrasound scan is one of the modalities which is helpful in diagnosing, and which may include all the following but not limited to: -\n\n- Kidney Stones\n- Gall Stones\n- Liver Cirrhosis or Fatty Liver\n- Blood Thrombosis\n- Specific Cases in Pregnancy Targeting Placenta Accreta\n- Thyroid Gland Disorders Such as Nodules and Goitres\n- Heart Failure Due to Hypertrophy and Valvular Defect\n- Inflammation Of the Pancreas\n- Abdominal Aortic Aneurism\n- Cysts And Fibroids Affecting the Structures of the Female Reproductive System\n- Injuries Affecting Muscles Tendons or Ligaments\n- Abscess Formation and Cellulitis\n\n## Preparing for Ultrasound Scan\n\n![Preparing for Ultrasound Scan](https://cadabams-diagnostics-assets.s3.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com/cadabam_assets/image-1731735992802-68116460.png)\n\nThere are different types of ultrasounds and there are also different indications for which the scan needs to be carried out, thus comparison here i think should not be done. However, below are broad principles, which may be useful in helping you obtain the ultrasound scan in a better way.\n\n### Prerequisites\n\nTo obtain clear results, the image formed on the abdominal scans might tilt or get worse as they cannot have any accumbent solids. On the other hand, the image scans on the Pelvic Region Ultrasound require a considerable amount of water consumption prior to its execution.\n\n### The Most Appropriate Time to Execute the Scan\n\nUltrasounds have numerous purposes; therefore, timing of the scan differs depending on the surgical or diagnostic requirement. For instance, after breakfast falls the time for abdominal ultrasound while Pelvic, MSK, and Doppler ultrasounds can occur in the afternoons too.\n\n### Who is Eligible for an Ultrasound Scan Examination?\n\nMost people, including children, pregnant women, and the elderly can undergo ultrasound procedures without feeling anxious about radiation exposure.\n\n### Procedure for Taking Ultrasound Scan\n\nYour sonographer is a trained ultrasound technician. To avoid friction, ultrasound gel is applied to your skin, after which the sonographer rubs an ultrasound transducer on your skin. Everything else is as easy as changing into a hospital gown.\n\nFor those who don’t know, a transducer is an ultrasound tool that is placed on skin to deliver sound waves to our body and receives echoes that are converted into images.\n\nIf the condition under examination is complex, or the area of the scan is, then the time required for the whole process may be longer than the average time frame of 15 – 45 minutes.\n\n### Caution Before Taking the Scan\n\nUltrasound scans are non-invasive and painless tests that most never require precautionary measures; however, recent surgeries or impediments should be conveyed to the healthcare provider. It is recommended that food consumption is avoided prior to undergoing an abdominal ultrasound, as this may aid in providing better results."
